article.headline: San Jose St. 59, Pacific 55
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Robert Owens scored a career-high 22 points and Justin Graham made a go-ahead 14-foot jumper with 11.1 seconds remaining to lift San Jose State to a 59-55 win over Pacific on Saturday. The Spartans closed the game with a 9-0 run after trailing most of the second half. Owens made a career-high six 3-pointers. C.J. Webster had 12 points and 14 rebounds and Adrian Oliver had 10 points and four assists for San Jose State (2-2). Michael Nunnally had 16 points and six rebounds and Lavar Neufville added 15 points for Pacific (4-1), which was off to its best start since 1998-99.
